summary: This is the ENB preset I currently use for playing Skyrim.  I simply upload this for any users of The Nexus who might like to use this for their game.
descriptionHtml:
I simply upload this preset as another ENB choice for users of The Nexus. It includes strong vibrant colours, realistic lighting and fairly high amounts of specular. I probably spent over two hundred hours tweaking the config whilst I was playing through the game so I believe it to be fairly solid and consistent.

[url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0132.htm]Download ENB SERIES 0.132. [/url] - Open Wrapper Version Folder and extract only \" d3d9.dll\" to  \"C:/ProgramFiles/Steam/Steamapps/Common/Skyrim/\"   to activate this ENB.


[color=red] Note: I did not use any Lighting mods except for Enhanced Lights and FX. I have not tested COT with this enb. [/color]

[b] It’s recommend to disable Anti Aliasing (AA) from Skyrim’s graphical options  This will provide the best performance with minor graphical loss. [/b]

[center] [heading][color=green]SETTING UP SkyrimPrefs.INI[/color] [/heading] 

Goto your SkyrimPrefs.ini file (typically found in C:/users/(computers name)/mydocuments/mygames/Skyrim/)



Find and alter the following lines to read.

bFloatPointRenderTarget=1 
bTreesReceiveShadows=1
bDrawLandShadows=1
bShadowsOnGrass=1

 [heading][color=green]Installation [/color] [/heading] [/center]

Open the Dark Fall ENB.Rar file. Extract all the files to your Skyrim folder (ie \"C:/ProgramFiles/Steam/Steamapps/Common/Skyrim/\").  

[url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0132.htm]Download ENB SERIES 0.132. [/url] - Open Wrapper Version Folder and extract only \" d3d9.dll\" to \"\"C:/ProgramFiles/Steam/Steamapps/Common/Skyrim/\" \"   to activate this ENB.
